         <entry xml:id="banei-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#baldar-dlgenr"
                next="#banariyot-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">בני</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">bny</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">banei</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">f.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <form type="inflected" opt="false">
               <orth type="inflected" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">בנוואן</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">bnwwʾn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">banavaʾn</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="num" opt="false">pl.</gram>"
      </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="banei-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">artefacts</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false"/>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" subtype="sense" xml:lang="en">
                  <quote>bath</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>bathhouse</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>βα(λα)νεῖον</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     רבנו הוה מתני שבחיה דר' חייה רובה קומי ר' ישמעאל בר' יוסי, אמר ליה יומא חד חמיתיה 
                     <app>
                        <lem>ביבני</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">ביבני</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox2 K V">בי בני</rdg>
                     </app> ולא איתכנע מיקמיי, אמר ליה ולמה לא איתכנעת מקומיה, אמר ליה מיסתכל הייתי באגדה דתילים, כיון דשמע כן מסר ליה תרי תלמידין והוו עלין עימיה לאשונה דלא ישהי ותזער נפשיה.
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">33,3</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 307: 4</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        Our Teacher was singing the praises of R. Ḥiyyah the Elder to R. Yishmaʿel b. R. Yose. Said he [R. Yishmaʿel b. Yose] to him: ‘One day I saw him [R. Ḥiyyah the Elder] at the baths but he did not make an obeisance before me.’ ‘Why did you not bow before him?’ inquired he [or Teacher]. ‘I was meditating on an Aggadah of the Psalms,’ he answered. On hearing this he gave him two disciples who used to go with him to the vapour room, lest he should stay too long and become enfeebled. (Freedman / Simon I 262)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     … <app>
                        <lem>דיתאזון</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#K">דיתזון</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat1">תיזון</rdg>
                     </app>
                     <app>
                        <lem>בני</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#K V">בי בני</rdg>
                     </app> תלתה יומין
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">63,8</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 690: 2</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation">
                     <quote>… you should heat the bath three days</quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
